{"lemma":"أَصَمِّ","slug":"أَصَمِّ","root":"ص.م.م","root_slug":"ص-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-م-م","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَصَمّ","root":"صمم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":12},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n24842","n24863"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"deaf"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause or render deaf, to deafen","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lose one's hearing, to become deaf","tags":["intransitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ص م م (ṣ m m)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.sˤamm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24842","headword_ar":"اصمّ","root":"Sm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", intrans.: see 1, first and fourth sentences.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASm~hu","text_ar":"اصمّهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God, S, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a disease, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered him deaf;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, * Msb, K; *) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused him to have a stoppage of the ear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a heaviness of hearing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSam~aniY AlkalaAma","text_ar":"اَصَمَّنِى الكَلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, diverted me from hearing the speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though he, or it, rendered me deaf. (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASm~hu","text_ar":"اصمّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, caused him to be as though he heard not."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b4-  And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, caused him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to utter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make, no sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like him who, not hearing, returns no reply to a call, or question;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be dumb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mute."},{"kind":"text","text":"] One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSam~a A@ll~`hu SadaAhu","text_ar":"اَصَمَّ ا@للّٰهُ صَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make his echo to return no sound;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God destroy him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) a prov., said in imprecating death upon a man; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sdy","text_ar":"صدي"},{"kind":"text","text":"being that which returns the like of his voice, or cry, from the mountains &c.; and when a man dies, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sdy","text_ar":"صدي"},{"kind":"text","text":"hears not from him anything that it should answer him, so that it is as though it were deaf. (Meyd.) [In the vulgar language, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sam~ama","text_ar":"صَمَّمَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"likewise signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He silenced him, reduced him to silence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"closed his mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says De Sacy, in his Chrest. Arabe, sec. ed., iii. 379.] ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASm~hu","text_ar":"اصمّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AaSomamahu","text_ar":"اَصْمَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He found him to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSam~","text_ar":"اَصَمّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deaf"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAdaAhu faA^aSam~ahu","text_ar":"نَادَاهُ فَاَصَمَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He called him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called to him, and found him to be deaf"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSam~a duEaAw^uhu","text_ar":"اَصَمَّ دُعَاوُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His call found persons deaf to it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who would not hear his censure."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-  See also 1, near the end."}],"source_refs":["God","S","Msb","K","TA","Th","M"]},{"entry_id":"n24863","headword_ar":"اَصَمُّ","root":"Sm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"applied to any animal, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Deaf;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * M, * Mgh, Msb, K; *) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a stoppage of the ear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a heaviness of hearing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sum~N","text_ar":"صُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sum~aAnN","text_ar":"صُمَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^aSam~u Eam~aA saA='ahu samiyEu"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) a prov., (Meyd,) meaning Feigning himself"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deaf to that which displeases him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd, TA,) i. e. to what is foul, (Meyd,) as though he heard it not, (TA,) but"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hearing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd, TA) that which pleases him, i. e. what is good; as does the generous man. (Meyd.) And similar is the saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waliY A^u*onN Eani AlfaHo$aA='i Sam~aA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I have an ear deaf to that which is foul"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also Ham p. 636, for another similar ex.] One says likewise,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEaAhu daEowapa AlA^aSam~i","text_ar":"دَعَاهُ دَعْوَةَ الاَصَمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He called him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the call of the deaf,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with extraordinary force."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Darabahu","text_ar":"ضَرَبَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daroba AlA^aSam~i","text_ar":"ضَرْبَ الاَصَمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He beat him"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the beating of the deaf,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uninterruptedly and excessively;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because the deaf, when he does thus, [not hearing any cry,] imagines that he is falling short of what he should do, and therefore will not leave off. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamaEa bivawobihi lamoEa AlA^aSam~i","text_ar":"لَمَعَ بِثَوْبِهِ لَمْعَ الاَصَمِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(one warning a people from afar)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made a sign by waving his garment continually, as does the deaf;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though he heard not the reply. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~apN A^aSam~u","text_ar":"حَيَّةٌ اَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A serpent that will not accept charming;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA;) as though it heard it not; (M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that will not obey the charmer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and [in like manner] the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sum~N","text_ar":"صُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to scorpions. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN A^aSam~u","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ اَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man whom one does not hope to win over, and who will not be turned back from the object of his desire;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA;) as though he were called and would not hear. (M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN A^aSam~u","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ اَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inexorable fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as though one complained to it and it would not hear. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~am~aA='u","text_ar":"الصَّمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAhiyapN Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"دَاهِيَةٌ صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SamaAmi","text_ar":"صَمَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonapN Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"فِتْنَةٌ صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sedition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the like,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is severe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard to be borne;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the allaying of which there is no way;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of its having gone to the utmost extent. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abokamu","text_ar":"اَبْكَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN A^aSam~u","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ اَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, that is severe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard to be borne."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SamamN","text_ar":"صَمَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is tropically attributed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHilom","text_ar":"الحِلْم"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) a poet, cited by Th, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qulo maA badaA laka mino zuwrK wamino ka*ibK\n                      \n                     \n                        HilomiY A^aSam~u waA^u*oniY gayoru Sam~aA='i"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [the last word I find written thus, app. for the sake of the rhyme: i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Say what occurs to thee, of falsehood and of lying: my forbearance is deaf,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insensible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"to it,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though my ear is not deaf"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaAp","text_ar":"قَطَاة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or bird of the species termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTFA","text_ar":"قَطًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and may in this case be rendered (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Small-eared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dull-eared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"being applied thereto] because of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakak","text_ar":"سَكَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. smallness &c.] of its ear or because it is deaf when thirsting. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSam~u","text_ar":"الاَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The deafmute"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an epithet applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajab","text_ar":"رَجَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) the month thus named, (Msb,) which the people of the Time of Ignorance called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahoru A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"شَهْرُ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSam~u","text_ar":"الاَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kh, S,) because the cry of the caller for aid was not heard in it, (Kh, S, M, Msb, K, *) shouting"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA lafulaAnK","text_ar":"يَا لَفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA SabaAHaAho","text_ar":"يَا صَبَاحَاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) nor the commotion of fight, (Kh, S, Msb,) nor the clash of arms, it being one of the sacred months: (Kh, S:) thus applied it is tropical, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAy^imN","text_ar":"نَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolN naAy^imN","text_ar":"لَيْلٌ نَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as though, in it, the man were deaf to the sound of arms: (TA:) and in like manner it is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munoSilu AlA^al~i","text_ar":"مُنْصِلُ الاَلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSab~u","text_ar":"الاَصَبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHar~amN","text_ar":"مُحَرَّمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahorN","text_ar":"شَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b2-  And [as that which is without a cavity is generally nonsonorous,] one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HajarN A^aSam~u","text_ar":"حَجَرٌ اَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hard"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and solid"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, &c.:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaxorapN Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"صَخْرَةٌ صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hard and solid rock:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or this latter signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rock in which is no crack nor hole:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sum~N","text_ar":"صُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanaApN","text_ar":"قَنَاةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A compact spear-shaft."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~am~aA='u","text_ar":"الصَّمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rugged ground:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sum~N","text_ar":"صُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-  Also [app. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The vermiform appendage of the cœcum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slender, extremity of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Efjp","text_ar":"عفجة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K: [the last word in this explanation is thus, without any syll. signs, in my MS. copy of the K and in the TA: in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eafijap","text_ar":"عَفِجَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the right reading is evidently"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eifajap","text_ar":"عِفَجَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said in the TA, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Efj","text_ar":"عفج"},{"kind":"text","text":", to be, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEofaAjN","text_ar":"اَعْفَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafajN","text_ar":"عَفَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and its dial. vars.: see this last word:] thus called [in my opinion because resembling a meatus auditorius that is closed, and therefore deaf; though said to be so called] because of its hardness. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN Sam~aA='u","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ صَمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fat she-camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and, (K,) or as some say, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one that has just conceived,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become pregnant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otimaAlu AlS~am~aA='i","text_ar":"اِشْتِمَالُ الصَّمَّا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, TA,) which is forbidden in a trad., (TA,) is (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The covering oneself with his garment, like"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as is done in the case of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imolap","text_ar":"شِمْلَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Arabs of the desert with their"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akosiyap","text_ar":"اَكْسِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A'Obeyd, S;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the turning the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the direction of one's right, upon his left arm and the part between his left shoulderjoint and neck, and then turning it a second time, from behind him, upon his right arm and the part between his right shoulder-joint and neck, so as to cover them both:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wrapping oneself with the garment without making to it a place from which to put forth the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or, (K,) as the lawyers explain it, (A'Obeyd, S,) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the wrapping one's body and arms with one garment, not having upon him another, and then raising it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the K, as is said in the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaDaEuhu","text_ar":"يَضَعُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarofaEuhu","text_ar":"يَرْفَعُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on one of its sides, and putting it upon his shoulder, so that his pudendum appears from it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, K:) [but] with the Arabs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libosapu AlS~am~aA='i","text_ar":"لِبْسَةُ الصَّمَّا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the covering one's whole body with his garment, and not raising a side from which to put forth his hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) when you say, of a man,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otamala AlS~am~aA='a","text_ar":"اِشْتَمَلَ الصَّمَّا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is as though you said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otamala","text_ar":"اِشْتَمَلَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~imolapa AlS~am~aA='a","text_ar":"الشِّمْلَةَ الصَّمَّا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~am~aA='","text_ar":"الصَّمَّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a sort of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otimaAl","text_ar":"اِشْتِمَال"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai$otamala","text_ar":"اِشْتَمَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~imolapu AlS~am~aA='u","text_ar":"الشِّمْلَةُ الصَّمَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ml","text_ar":"شمل"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*orN A^aSam~u","text_ar":"جَذْرٌ اَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A surd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an irrational, root, in arithmetic;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is known only to God, accord. to a saying of 'Áïsheh: opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*orN naATiqN","text_ar":"جَذْرٌ نَاطِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j*r","text_ar":"جذر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolN A^aSam~u","text_ar":"فِعْلٌ اَصَمُّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A surd verb"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1725},{"kind":"text","text":"is a term sometimes used in grammar, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a triliteral-radical verb of the class commonly called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDaAEafN","text_ar":"مُضَاعَفٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the second and third radicals are the same letter."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","M","K","Msb","TA","Meyd","S","Kh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}